The Rallying Point: My Story Of The New Guard
by Eric Campbell (1965)

The New Guard was an Australian Monarchist and Anti-Communist group, which has been described as fascist. It was founded by Eric Campbell, a World War 1 Veteran in 1931. It had a peak membership of over 50,000 and was known for breaking up Communist meetings and even beating up the founder of the Communist Party of Australia. The group came close to starting a coup d'etat against Jack Lang's NSW government. When Jack Lang was dismissed as premier, group membership dropped significantly.

Later, Eric Campbell became interested in fascism and met with Oswald Mosley, but failed to meet with Hitler and Mussolini. He was deeply impressed by fascism and tried to transition the New Guard to fascism, which led to further decline due to members unhappy with the new fascist stance. 

After failing to win the 1935 election, Campbell withdrew from public life.
